  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "AWS Cloud Engineer",
  "description": "<p>We are representing our client in the global technology and engineering space to look for a Senior Engineer specializing in Amazon Web Services (AWS) to join their dynamic Cloud Business Unit. In this role, you will support the organization’s mission of delivering cutting-edge data centre and cloud services by designing, securing, implementing, and managing scalable and secure cloud solutions for a broad range of clients.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Design, implement, secure, and manage scalable AWS cloud solutions.</li><li>Operate and maintain AWS cloud environments at scale.</li><li>Deliver and manage large-scale cloud projects from execution through to delivery, including work within highly regulated environments.</li><li>Apply security best practices, networking principles, and identity management within AWS.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve complex technical challenges in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams while also working independently when required.</li><li>Communicate technical concepts clearly to diverse audiences.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience operating AWS cloud environments at scale.</li><li>Strong proficiency with AWS services, including EC2, S3, VPC, Lambda, RDS, IAM, and CloudWatch.</li><li>Strong understanding of networking concepts, security best practices, and identity and access management in AWS.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving skills and strong attention to detail.</li><li>Strong communication skills.</li><li>Relevant AWS certifications are highly desirable.</li><li>Hands-on experience with automation and configuration management tools such as CloudFormation, Terraform, Ansible, or similar.</li><li>Familiarity with containerisation technologies such as Docker and orchestration platforms like Kubernetes is a plus.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
